we are talking tax cuts not increases .

give a guy who is spending $ 1 million a year a $ 10,000 tax break gets you 1 % growth among the handful of rich guys .
consumption goes right into gdp growth and it gets multiplied quickly .

much of what is reported in this interesting piece is aided and abetted by ... instant communications ; it becomes a catch-22 : the means of communicating to millions anytime feeds on itself .
thinking time is short because the ability to deliver a message is there , waiting and -- worse -- the pres .
is a tweet junkie .
so many mistakes or " mispeaking " or " missteps " occur simply because there is little time to reflect , and a decision to " say nothing right now " is rare .
that 's the sending end .
on the receiving end , much of the public are now 24/7 news junkies , slavering for updates even when there really are n't any .
legitimacy is threatened .
hence , " fake news . "
just a century ago , it was different : no instant mass communication .
as most people did not live in cities , many never read one of the handful of daily newspapers .
many were illiterate , most had no telephone .
news travelled more slowly ; next week was good enough .
result : less " news . "
not today .
result : chaos reign

much of what is reported in this interesting piece is aided and abetted by ... instant communications ; it becomes a catch-22 : the means of communicating to millions anytime feeds on itself .
thinking time is short because the ability to deliver a message is there , waiting and -- worse -- the pres .
is a tweet junkie .
so many mistakes or " mispeaking " or " missteps " occur simply because there is little time to reflect , and a decision to " say nothing right now " is rare .
that 's the sending end .
on the receiving end , much of the public are now 24/7 news junkies , slavering for updates even when there really are n't any .
legitimacy is threatened .
hence , " fake news . "
just a century ago , it was different : no instant mass communication .
as most people did not live in cities , many never read one of the handful of daily newspapers .
many were illiterate , most had no telephone .
news travelled more slowly ; next week was good enough .
result : less " news . "
not today .
result : chaos reign

morning 
 in accounting you need to reflect the invoice cost in your books which would r 25 / kg in this example .
the rebates are generally as a percentage and are services rendered separate from the invoice .
as originally pointed out the removal of the rebate system and its replacement by a normal distribution model would not necessarily change the price of the goods in the consumers ' hands and neither would it change the income actually received by the producer .
on the basis that the rebate income is fully utilised for the marketing of the particular lot or consignment that is linked to there is no financial benefit to the retailer .
it merely understates your gross margin which is useful marketing bumpf for the retailer .
if not all the rebate income is used for its supposed purpose it becomes other income and is a direct benefit to the retailer .

the proposed changes do not stop doctors , nor others , from incorporating .
they are about ensuring a level tax playing field between those who choose to incorporate and those who do not .
dr. avery says nothing about why the proposed tax changes will make it difficult or impossible for doctors to save for retirement .
they have exactly the same opportunities as the rest of us , rrsp 's and tfsa 's .
they also can create formal pension schemes within their corporations as long as they are treated as employees within their own corporations .
the proposed tax changes are about not spreading ( i.e. sprinkling ) income unfairly ( unreasonably ) across family members unless they do actual work for the corporation , and not making market investments within the tax protected corporate boundaries .

the problem with disincentives for degrees that are not in demand is that it takes four or five years to get a bachelors degree , typically two or three years after that to get a master 's or professional degree , although some of the master 's equivalent professional degrees take four years , and at least a couple of years after that to get a ph.d. in other words , it typically takes about eight years of university to get a professional degree ( ll .
b , m.d , d.d.s and the like )   or ten years of university to get a ph.d. 

 to make sense , the disincentives would have to be for degrees that will not be in demand when this year 's first year class graduates .

trump quotes now available on demand 
 
 you can now get donald trump 's best and worst quotes on demand via facebook messenger , thanks to a new presidential candidate bot known as bff trump .
the bot greets users with the following message : ‚Äú hi .
this is me , bff trump !
i have opinions on everything from walls to women . ‚Äù
it then proceeds to spit out quotes from the republican candidate , ranging from his views on black youth to crying babies .

option .

morning 
 in accounting you need to reflect the invoice cost in your books which would r 25 / kg in this example .
the rebates are generally as a percentage and are services rendered separate from the invoice .
as originally pointed out the removal of the rebate system and its replacement by a normal distribution model would not necessarily change the price of the goods in the consumers ' hands and neither would it change the income actually received by the producer .
on the basis that the rebate income is fully utilised for the marketing of the particular lot or consignment that is linked to there is no financial benefit to the retailer .
it merely understates your gross margin which is useful marketing bumpf for the retailer .
if not all the rebate income is used for its supposed purpose it becomes other income and is a direct benefit to the retailer .

the problem with disincentives for degrees that are not in demand is that it takes four or five years to get a bachelors degree , typically two or three years after that to get a master 's or professional degree , although some of the master 's equivalent professional degrees take four years , and at least a couple of years after that to get a ph.d. in other words , it typically takes about eight years of university to get a professional degree ( ll .
b , m.d , d.d.s and the like )   or ten years of university to get a ph.d. 

 to make sense , the disincentives would have to be for degrees that will not be in demand when this year 's first year class graduates .

the " patriarchal " interpretation of the tob is manifested by viewing man and woman as gender stereotypes based on bodily anatomy , rather than viewing man and woman   as integral personal subjects .
this kind of misinterpretation of the tob has been widely disseminated , in recent times , as a way to rationalize traditional patriarchal practices such as the exclusively male priesthood , which was based on ancient gender theory ( the idea that " women are defective males , " as in aristotle and aquinas ) .
the same applies to " love and responsibility , " which is even more focused on responsible parenthood and was never intended to cover the entire sacramental life of the church , including holy orders .

the american system does not , and never did go by majority populous vote .
people vote for their electoral college representative according to their party ( d / r. )    the ec is made up of one   representative from each county in the country .
the ec decides who appointed to the oval office by the preponderance of party - line votes in each county .
trump won 309 ec votes and clinton 217 ( ? ) ) .
it balances high - density populations of cities like boston , new york and philadelphia , and low - density rural ridings ( much like toronto and the rest of ontario ) .
that is just how it works and nothing is going to change it .

laicization is easier to understand if you think , not in terms of priesthood and sacramental ordination , but in terms of the clerical state and clerical status .
laicization at least assumes the validity of ordination , but definitively removes the authority of the cleric to act as a cleric would except in emergencies and other closely defined instances ( like teaching in a catholic school , college , university or seminary ) .
the only other status that church law recognizes is the lay state , hence a man [ sic ] who has lost his clerical " privileges " is said to be " reduced to the lay state , " to obviate any consideration of the laicized man exercising clerical or priestly functions without further action by the holy see .

the factors leading people to move can be complex .
often the causes are multi - faceted .
migrants may move across international borders to improve their lives by finding work , or in some cases for education , family reunion , or other reasons .
people may also move to alleviate significant hardships that arise from natural disasters , famine , or extreme poverty .
those who leave their countries for these reasons would not usually be considered refugees under international law .

the war on drugs in canada increasingly focuses on cannabis .
in 2011 , cannabis offences accounted for 69 % of all drug offences , simple possession accounted for 70 % of all drug offences , and of these , 54 % were for cannabis possession -- an increase of 7 % since 2010 .

online voting is vastly different than online tax returns or online banking .
all they are trying to secure is the connection using encryption .
with online voting we must be sure the individual casting an online vote is in fact the person they claim to be .
which is why we physically cast our ballots at polling stations .
online voting opens up the door for parents to cast the votes of at age live at home children .
it opens the door for one spouse to cast the others ballot .
one of the most basic fundamentals of a democracy is " one person , one vote " .
until a time when we can ensure an online voter is how they claim to be , we must continue to cast our ballots in person .

the factors leading people to move can be complex .
often the causes are multi - faceted .
migrants may move across international borders to improve their lives by finding work , or in some cases for education , family reunion , or other reasons .
people may also move to alleviate significant hardships that arise from natural disasters , famine , or extreme poverty .
those who leave their countries for these reasons would not usually be considered refugees under international law .

the war on drugs in canada increasingly focuses on cannabis .
in 2011 , cannabis offences accounted for 69 % of all drug offences , simple possession accounted for 70 % of all drug offences , and of these , 54 % were for cannabis possession -- an increase of 7 % since 2010 .
in 2012 , there were 109,455 drug offences in canada , 52 % were for cannabis possession .
in 2010 and 2011 , possession of cannabis still comprised over half of all drug offences . " (
2014 , boyd & carter ; killer weed ) .
one might surmise that " increases in drug offences often reflect police practices such as increased attention to particular categories of crime " ( ibid ) . "
charges for possession of cannabis in bc have doubled between 2005 and 2011 despite low public support fro the imposition of a criminal conviction for this offence " ( ibid ) .

first , it seems appropriate to place that burden on a future generation because any benefit from rail lives in the future .
borrowing for infrastructure projects at this historical moment is affordable .
second , my arguments are not circular .

laicization is easier to understand if you think , not in terms of priesthood and sacramental ordination , but in terms of the clerical state and clerical status .
laicization at least assumes the validity of ordination , but definitively removes the authority of the cleric to act as a cleric would except in emergencies and other closely defined instances ( like teaching in a catholic school , college , university or seminary ) .
the only other status that church law recognizes is the lay state , hence a man [ sic ] who has lost his clerical " privileges " is said to be " reduced to the lay state , " to obviate any consideration of the laicized man exercising clerical or priestly functions without further action by the holy see .

online voting is vastly different than online tax returns or online banking .
all they are trying to secure is the connection using encryption .
with online voting we must be sure the individual casting an online vote is in fact the person they claim to be .
which is why we physically cast our ballots at polling stations .
online voting opens up the door for parents to cast the votes of at age live at home children .
it opens the door for one spouse to cast the others ballot .
one of the most basic fundamentals of a democracy is " one person , one vote " .
until a time when we can ensure an online voter is how they claim to be , we must continue to cast our ballots in person .

as far as interracial crime goes :  
 of the nearly 770,000 violent interracial crimes committed every year involving blacks and whites , blacks commit 85 percent and whites commit 15 percent .
blacks commit more violent crime against whites than against blacks .
forty - five percent of their victims are white , 43 percent are black , and 10 percent are hispanic .
when whites commit violent crime , only three percent of their victims are black .
blacks are an estimated 39 times more likely to commit a violent crime against a white than vice versa , and 136 times more likely to commit robbery .
blacks are 2.25 times more likely to commit officially - designated hate crimes against whites than vice versa .
as far as criminal gangs 
 only 10 percent of youth gang members are white .
hispanics are 19 times more likely than whites to be members of youth gangs .
blacks are 15 times more likely , and asians are nine times more likely .
that 's the data .

i 've been doing objective research for 25 years , and what i 've found is that a relatively small cabal of self - interested meteorologists whose livelihoods depend on government jobs and/or research grants have contrived a theory based on a relatively small 200 year snapshot of the earth 's 4.6 billion year history that presumes capitalist - fed industrialization is the primary cause of what was formerly called " global warming " and is now called " climate change " ( because it has n't warmed significantly for 20 years ) , in order to get grant money .
there is no scientific evidence whatsoever that shows increases in co2 to be a significant cause of global warming .
history , going back 4.6 billion years , shows wide swings of both temperature and co2 concentrations , with temperature always rising before the co2 level rises .
the climate always changes , and not because of co2 .
the ipcc is a political organization , not a scientific one .

as a tax preparer , i 've seen yet another often overlooked error .
an employee starts to receive cpp and elects to stop making cpp contributions ( age appropriate ) , but continues to work with the same employer .
the employer will often continue to make cpp deductions ....    when they finally ( in this case after three years ) stop deducting , they will continue to put the cpp pensionable earnings in box 26 on the t4 slip at the full amount , instead of zero .
( makes it also tough to complete schedule 8 , and the employer must then cancel the original t4 slip and submit a new one with zero in box 26 . )

many people question the effectiveness of our education system in alaska .

there is no scientific evidence whatsoever that shows increases in co2 to be a significant cause of global warming .

the climate always changes , and not because of co2 .

as far as interracial crime goes :  
 of the nearly 770,000 violent interracial crimes committed every year involving blacks and whites , blacks commit 85 percent and whites commit 15 percent .
blacks commit more violent crime against whites than against blacks .
forty - five percent of their victims are white , 43 percent are black , and 10 percent are hispanic .
when whites commit violent crime , only three percent of their victims are black .
blacks are an estimated 39 times more likely to commit a violent crime against a white than vice versa , and 136 times more likely to commit robbery .
blacks are 2.25 times more likely to commit officially - designated hate crimes against whites than vice versa .
as far as criminal gangs 
 only 10 percent of youth gang members are white .
hispanics are 19 times more likely than whites to be members of youth gangs .
blacks are 15 times more likely , and asians are nine times more likely .
that 's the data .
